
Overview of noun detection

The noun detection has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (4) detection, sensing -- (the perception that something has occurred or some state exists; "early detection can often lead to a cure")
2. (2) detection, catching, espial, spying, spotting -- (the act of detecting something; catching sight of something)
3. signal detection, detection -- (the detection that a signal is being received)
4. detection, detecting, detective work, sleuthing -- (a police investigation to determine the perpetrator; "detection is hard on the feet")
